  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Market 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Market">
A <b>Market</b> is the identification of a marketing segment for products.
			</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Market  Attribute: name 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Market.name">
the words by which the market is known.
				</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Market  Attribute: market_segment_type 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Market.market_segment_type">
     <p>
the text that identifies a marketing category of products.
     </p>
<example>'Luxur
y automobiles', 'laptop personal computers', and 'budget personal stereos' are examples of
market segment types.
</example>

				</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept">
A <b>Product_concept</b> is the identification of a set of similar products that were, are or will be proposed to customers.
<note number="1">The definition of product concepts is driven by market and customer requirements and
forecasting. A <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> often corresponds to the highest level item(s) manufactured by an organization
for customers. </note>
<example number="1">In an organization which manufactures cars and engines for cars, the car models will be represented by instances of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>. 
</example>
<note number="2">The entity data type <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> enables to represent customer-oriented identification of products that are to be delivered to customers, 
while the entity data type Product enables to identify and to track the history of items that are designed and manufactured, as a tangible solution, or component of the solution, for a product concept. 
</note>
<note number="3">A product concept may be characterized by a set of product features identified by the customers or derived from
customers' needs. 
</note>
<note number="4">Depending on the kind of industry and products, a product concept might be offered to the customers in
one or many different configurations.
</note>
			</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Attribute: id 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description
linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.id">
     <p>
       the identifying string that distinguishes the <express_ref
       linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>. 
   </p>
<example number="2">The id may be a sales model number.
</example>
				</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Attribute: name 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.name">
the words by which the <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> is known.
				</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Attribute: description 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.description">
the text that characterizes the <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>. The value of the attribute need not be
specified.
				</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Attribute: target_market 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description
     linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.target_market">
     <p>
       the <express_ref
linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Market"/>
for which the <express_ref
linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/>
is intended. The value of the attribute need not be specified.
   </p>
<note number="5">In the MIM schema, the corresponding attribute is mandatory and refers to the entity data type <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_concept_context"/>. If <b>target_market</b> is not specified, 
empty strings shall be assigned to the attributes name and <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Market.market_segment_type"/> of the instance of <express_ref linkend="application_context_schema:ir_express:application_context_schema.product_concept_context"/>.
</note>
	</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Unique: UR1 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.ur:UR1">
there shall not be, in the data set, another instance of <express_ref linkend="product_concept_identification:arm:Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept"/> with the same id.
		</ext_description>
		
  <!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Product_concept_identification_arm  Entity: Product_concept  Where: IP1 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description
linkend="Product_concept_identification_arm.Product_concept.wr:IP1">
     <p>
       <b>id</b> and <b>name</b> shall not be both no-word strings.
     </p>
   	</ext_description>		
</ext_descriptions>